OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784607479
OL,3,CIs a fourth UK heatwave brewing?
OL,5,FWhen there is more sun, it will be
OL,6,Fpleasantly warm or hot in England and
OL,7,FWales, with the current heatwave
OL,8,Fcontinuing in the southwest.
OL,10,FBut it'll be nowhere near the heat of
OL,11,Fa couple of weeks ago, which saw
OL,12,Ftemperatures peak close to 35.5C.
OL,14,FThis week, we will sit comfortably in
OL,15,Fthe mid to high 20s - around 25-28C in
OL,16,Fmost southern spots, and lower for the
OL,17,Fnorth and northwest.
OL,19,FIs any rain forecast next week?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784607479
OL,3,CIs a fourth UK heatwave brewing?
OL,5,FParts of the south and southeast have
OL,6,Fnot recorded any rainfall at all this
OL,7,Fmonth.
OL,9,FThe only significant wet weather this
OL,10,Fweek is expected in some areas of
OL,11,Fnorthwest Scotland.
OL,13,FOver the weekend, parts of the north
OL,14,Fand northwest are also forecast to get
OL,15,Fsome showery rain.
OL,17,FThere is a hint that a weather system
OL,18,Fbringing rain will drift in from the
OL,19,Fnorthwest by the middle of next week,
OL,20,Fand this will journey south.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
